---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
	title="Governance | The Sovereign Protocol of Tadpole OS"
	description="The ethical and technical framework for local-first multi-agent systems. Understanding the Overlord Protocol and Sovereign Execution."
>
	<main class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="space-y-12">
      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="space-y-4 border-b border-zinc-900 pb-12">
        <a href="/" class="text-sm font-mono text-zinc-500 hover:text-white transition-colors flex items-center gap-2">
          ← RETURN TO BASE
        </a>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white">
          The <span class="text-zinc-400">Sovereign Protocol</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-zinc-500 font-mono">
          VERSION 1.0.0 | GOVERNANCE & ETHICS WHITE-PAPER
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Section: The Overlord -->
      <section class="space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold border-l-2 border-zinc-800 pl-4">I. The Overlord (Entity 0)</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
          <p>
            In the Tadpole OS ecosystem, the human operator is designated as **Entity 0**, also known as **The Overlord**. Unlike traditional AI systems where the user is a passive observer, the Overlord is the active heart of the swarm.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Final Authority</strong>: No agent may execute a destructive or high-risk tool without explicit encryption-checked approval from Entity 0.</li>
            <li><strong>Strategic Directive</strong>: Intelligence flows downward. The Overlord provides the "Global Intent," which is recursively decomposed by sub-agents into tactical execution steps.</li>
            <li><strong>The Safety Gate</strong>: A dedicated Oversight Dashboard ensures every LLM-generated decision is visible, auditable, and retractable in real-time.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section: Local-First Sovereignty -->
      <section class="space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold border-l-2 border-zinc-800 pl-4">II. Sovereign Execution</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
          <p>
            Data sovereignty is not just a feature—it is a fundamental right. Small and medium businesses (SMBs) often face the choice between high-cost cloud compliance or low-intelligence local tools. Tadpole OS breaks this dichotomy.
          </p>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 my-8">
            <div class="p-6 bg-zinc-950/50 border border-zinc-900 rounded-xl">
              <h4 class="font-bold text-white mb-2">Private Context</h4>
              <p class="text-sm">Strategic intelligence and proprietary data never leave your local hardware. The "Brain" of your company remains yours alone.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 bg-zinc-950/50 border border-zinc-900 rounded-xl">
              <h4 class="font-bold text-white mb-2">Agent Accountability</h4>
              <p class="text-sm">Every agent action is logged locally in high-performance SQLite ledgers, creating a permanent, immutable record of decision-making.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section: Scaling Small Teams -->
      <section class="space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold border-l-2 border-zinc-800 pl-4">III. The Scalability Matrix</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
          <p>
            Tadpole OS enables one person to manage the output of twenty. Our recursive architecture ensures that even as complexity scales, the "cognitive load" on the Overlord remains manageable.
          </p>
          <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-zinc-400 pl-6 italic text-lg text-zinc-300 my-8">
            "We believe the next unicorn companies will be founded by teams of less than five people, powered by sovereign swarms of over fifty agents."
          </blockquote>
          <p>
            By leveraging Rust-powered concurrency and triple-slot model routing, SMBs can deploy specialized agents (Security Audit, DevOps, Marketing, Research) simultaneously, creating a hyper-efficient "Virtual Corporation."
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Footer CTA -->
      <footer class="pt-24 border-t border-zinc-900 text-center space-y-6">
        <p class="text-zinc-500 font-mono text-sm tracking-widest">END OF DOCUMENT</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
          <a href="https://github.com/DDS-Solutions/TadPole-OS" class="w-full sm:w-auto px-8 py-3 bg-white text-zinc-950 font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-zinc-200 transition-colors">
            Start Scaling
          </a>
          <a href="/" class="w-full sm:w-auto px-8 py-3 bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-zinc-800 transition-colors text-zinc-400">
            Back to Home
          </a>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </div>
	</main>
</BaseLayout>
